-----
[[include :scp-wiki:component:image-block
|name=https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/local--files/drapricus-author-page/sunshine
|caption=A visual representation of the ray of sunshine[[footnote]] Fun fact: my alias on the Wiki, "Apricus," is Latin for sunshine. [[/footnote]] that I am.
|width=300px
]]

I'm [[*user DrApricus]][[footnote]] Apricus, DrApricot, Apricot, Apri, and whatever sick and twisted nicknames you can come up with are all acceptable stand-ins. [[/footnote]], and I'm a quote-unquote "author" here on the SCP Wiki. I'm known for such renowned works as [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-6725 the wall that you run into] and [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-5400-j that one unfunny joke]. I also contributed to the [https://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/scp-7779 complete and total eradication of France] and beat Dead Ahead on Hard Mode in Hotline Miami 2. Needless to say, I'm pretty frickin' awesome.

Occasionally, I'll write some garbage that people like (or maybe you're one of the many people who hate it) and post it here on the Wiki, but a lot of times, I like to read other people's works and help new and aspiring authors get acclimated to the site. I am **ALWAYS**[[footnote]] I do occasionally take brief, unannounced, intermittent breaks from the Wiki. That is the only circumstance in which I am unavailable. [[/footnote]] available to give you any advice, show you around, and help you get your first article up on the site. I do both idea critique and draft critique, but I especially prefer looking at ideas and hearing elevator pitches.

As far as my preferences on //what// I prefer to critique go, while I'm willing to critique virtually anything, my specialties are astronomical[[footnote]] This can range from cosmic horror to physics-heavy space stuff to lighthearted extraterrestrial species of crabs. [[/footnote]] concepts, detailed paranormal science, musical anomalies, character development pieces, heavy dialogue, internal Foundation affairs, bureaucratic mumbo jumbo, comedy[[footnote]] It is important to note that I am **NOT** funny whatsoever. [[/footnote]], philosophical topics, and anything related to dogs (strictly excluding animal cruelty). My aversions are the typical icky stuff, such as [[span style="color: transparent; text-shadow: 0 0 5px rgba(0,0,0,0.5);"]]sexual abuse and rape, child abuse, violent hate crimes[[footnote]] This means violent acts perpetrated because of racism, sexism, homophobia, transphobia, xenophobia, religious discrimination, etc. [[/footnote]], self-harm, gratuitous sexual content or violence, and, as aforementioned, animal cruelty[[/span]]. I do make exceptions, such as with heavily critical social commentary, but generally speaking, avoid coming to me with elevator pitches and drafts that focus a lot on those topics.

If you want to reach out to me for any reason, be it you want me to look at something, or you're interested in a collaboration, the two best methods are through Wikidot PMs and the [https://discord.gg/scp official SCP Discord], with the latter being the quickest way to get a response from me. As I said earlier, you are always welcome to contact me; my door is always open. Importantly, note that if I come across as awkward or caustic, that is not your doing in any regard[[footnote]] Unless I explicitly say otherwise, and I will! I am not subtle. [[/footnote]], that is @@ @@ [[span class="stretch"]]all[[/span]] @@ @@ me. If I don't get back to you within 24 hours, start annoying me, and if I don't get back to you within 72 hours, assume I'm either on hiatus or dead.

Now, onto the fun part: here are my **Top 5** articles that I am most proud of[[footnote]] Total rating does not equate to how proud I am of a published work of mine. [[/footnote]], in order of how proud of them I am.

[[div class="block"]]
[[div style="margin-top: 1.5%;"]]
[[module ListPages name="scp-8350" limit="1"]]
[[div class="au-preview {$background}"]]
[[size 150%]]**%%title_linked%%**[[/size]]@@  @@//Public Affairs//
 +**{{%%rating%%}}**
//"You ask ten doctors what's wrong with a patient, there is going to be at least one dissenter. [...] If we bend world leaders to our side and make the world population doubt their own senses and reasoning, our sole, uncontested narrative will effectively become truth."//

##000|Public Affairs is tasked with controlling the media and global narrative to serve the interests of the Foundation, but the department is long overdue for an upgrade. Meanwhile, containing an unruly species of shapeshifters and deceivers proves to be a difficult puzzle for the Polymorphs Department. After a crucial secret is revealed, Site-322 may just have the solution to both issues in this lighthearted, comedic episode of the Integration Program.##
[[/div]]
[[/module]]
[[/div]]

[[module ListPages name="scp-7099" limit="1"]]
[[div class="au-preview {$background}"]]
[[size 150%]]**%%title_linked%%**[[/size]]@@  @@//A-Net: Radio Made Fun!™//
##000|**Collaboration with**## [[*user Voiiiii]]
 +**{{%%rating%%}}**
//"Ryan Seacrest was quickly taken into Foundation custody following the events of the previous addendum. Personnel believed doing so would cause SCP-7099-A to be absent or for the broadcast to be delayed."//

##000|In this day and age where everyone has their own podcast, and anyone can access an infinite stream of short-form content from a box in their hand, some might claim that the medium of radio is dead. Of course, they haven't heard of A-Net Radio, the titular eccentric radio station in this supernatural psych horror.##
[[/div]]
[[/module]]

[[module ListPages name="scp-7421" limit="1"]]
[[div class="au-preview {$background}"]]
[[size 150%]]**%%title_linked%%**[[/size]]@@  @@//Wartrod Hanging//
 +**{{%%rating%%}}**
//"...one of the condemned left hanging from SCP-7421, an unidentified male with a severely injured face, was still breathing. Later investigation found he had been hanging for 58 years as of 1914."//

##000|The Wild West is known in film and television cliches for its wide desert landscapes, arid mountainous scenery, beautiful accompanying scores, and Clint Eastwood smoking an inexpensive cigar. But there exists a much more sinister side to the history of the Wild West, with violent injustices that are continuing to resurface in our society today. Whether or not there is a heaven and hell, the victims in this gruesome body horror pray there is.##
[[/div]]
[[/module]]

[[module ListPages name="scp-6725" limit="1"]]
[[div class="au-preview {$background}"]]
[[size 150%]]**%%title_linked%%**[[/size]]@@  @@//Mind-Blowing Wall Art//
 +**{{%%rating%%}}**
//"Contact with the task force is lost after authorization to shoot to kill is granted to the operatives. CCTV shows the task force dropping their rifles and charging into the fire."//

##000|Postmodern art: when the rejection of Enlightenment breeds abstraction and confusion and where it seems meaning goes to die. Nevertheless, it utterly captivates the world. In this absurdist piece, "meaning" is people, and "captivates" has a fluid definition, but rest assured you will be and stay captivated. Wile E. Coyote, meet Road Runner.##
[[/div]]
[[/module]]

[[module ListPages name="scp-6264" limit="1"]]
[[div class="au-preview {$background}"]]
[[size 150%]]**%%title_linked%%**[[/size]]@@  @@//Temperature Tantrum//
##000|**Collaboration with**## [[*user LAN 2D]]
 +**{{%%rating%%}}**
//"...an anonymous tip was received by the Foundation Complaints Office, accusing SCP-6264-G of abusing his position's power within the Foundation hierarchy, corruption, embezzlement, and, most notably, impersonation of Foundation personnel."//

##000|Office disputes are nothing new -- they're as old as corporations themselves. But these disputes carry heavier risks when that office is responsible for containing anomalies and phenomena where any slip-up could cause someone to croak. When two fine-as-frog-hair employees begin butting heads, the higher-ups learn that resolving the conflict in this abstract comedy is like herding frogs. ##
[[/div]]
[[/module]]
[[/div]]

And now for an honorable mention!

[[div class="block"]]
[[div style="margin-top: 1.5%;"]]
[[module ListPages name="scp-7779" limit="1"]]
[[div class="au-preview {$background}"]]
[[size 150%]]**%%title_linked%%**[[/size]]@@  @@//LE POOF!//
##000|**Collaboration with**## [[*user Aftokrator]]##000|,## [[*user Fish^12]]##000|, and## [[*user Jack Waltz]]
 +**{{%%rating%%}}**
//"France's sudden disappearance generated a massive vacuum, causing air and seawater to rush into the vacant space. The explosion generated in these vacuums led to strong winds blowing across western Europe."//

##000|I was sitting in my European History class one day when I thought to myself, "Hey, what if France just vanished?" Apparently, this was a very popular question and several months later, my co-authors hopped on board to bring this absurd geopolitical piece to fruition. Inspired by the Broken Masquerade canon, sit and watch as the disappearance of the country of France almost ends the world. Note: This SCP is not meant to display hate towards or prejudice against French people.##
[[/div]]
[[/module]]
[[/div]]
[[/div]]

Finally, here's a comprehensive list of all my standing works.

[[module ListPages created_by="DrApricus" separate="no" order="rating desc" prependLine="||~ SCP ||~ Rating ||~ Comments ||~ Created ||~ Last Comment ||~ Length ||"]]
|| %%title_linked%% || %%rating%% || %%comments%% || %%created_at%% || %%commented_at%% || %%size%% ||
[[/module]]

If I cannot be contacted for over a year for any reason and without prior notice, all my published works are to be indefinitely relinquished (until my return) to the community and made available for rewrite without my consultation should they meet all other existing criteria. In such a scenario, I urge Wiki staff to take the measures they deem fit to resolve any issues that may arise concerning my articles, such as licensing problems, again without my consultation. In this scenario, I would retain all original authorship credit under Creative Commons. This shouldn't ever be a concern, but better safe than sorry.

@@ @@
[[=]]
[[collapsible show="+ WHAT'S NEXT?" hide="-"]]
[[<]]
> For a while now, I've felt like I have gotten far too comfortable with my writing here on the Wiki. I feel as if I have found what I am --really good-- //least bad// at and, intentionally or not, stuck to that. For me to grow as a writer, I need to be willing to leave my comfort zone, build worlds, commit to those worlds and their characters, and continue to make my latest my best. While I will still be writing other content because I can do whatever the hell I want, for the next year or longer, I will be working in the background on a project I have been letting ferment in my head for a while now...
> = [[size 150%]]**//SHIELDS AKIMBO//**[[/size]]
> ...aka, my obsession with cool sci-fi AI shit come to life. This will be a four-part series, each "episode" being fairly lengthy and devoted to a product of "Shields Akimbo," a covert project by an especially cold Foundation that aims to protect the collective human population of the Earths through our many parallel universes from the paranormal and supernatural. Each episode will be written so as to intertwine together to create an overarching story, but my hope is that they will still be able to suffice as standalone reads. 
> 
> I aim to have the first episode published by the end of this year, though I'm unsure how realistic that goal is. But anyway, below are a few little teasers I made while procrastinating on my actual responsibilities.
[[/<]]

